makeNewXenaFile

public java.io.File makeNewXenaFile(XenaInputSource input,
                                    AbstractNormaliser normaliser,
                                    java.io.File destinationDir)
                             throws XenaException
Description copied from class: AbstractFileNamer
This abstract method creates a new Xena file. This must be implemented by any concrete file namers. The concrete implmentation must create a file, based on some or all of the inputs (or none if you like!). A XenaException should be thrown in the case of the file not being able to be created. Additionally, the flag 'overwrite' may be interrogated or ignored depending on the implementation of the specific fileNamer.

Specified by:
makeNewXenaFile in class AbstractFileNamer
Returns:
File - the new Xena file.
Throws:
XenaException - - in the event of an error creating the file.
